<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16127] OrderedExecutor can orphan permits and leak locks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16127</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a thread is interrupted while waiting to acquire a maxThreads semaphore permit, then it does not clean up the corresponding entry in striped lock, which may prevent future threads from executing even when enough semaphore permits become available.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
